description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title – Bank Facilities Assistant&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base – Charlton Lane Hospital and Cheltenham Localities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary – £9.21 to £9.89 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking for a flexible role in a friendly and enthusiastic Team? We have the perfect opportunity for you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for Bank Facilities Assistants, enthusiastic and flexible individuals to work within the Facilities Team at Charlton Lane Hospital and Cheltenham Localities. The role will be working in both catering &amp; cleaning.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Charlton Lane Hospital is a 3-ward refurbished hospital which opened in the summer of 2010. It provides specialist assessment, treatment and care forolder people withfunctional mental health problems and people with dementia.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you enjoy working in an active and busy role with a team around you, and have great communication skills, with previous experience working within catering, or cleaning or even both, then we would welcome an application from you.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For an informal discussion and any enquires please contact Inga Manugiewicz, Facilities Manager, on 01242 634 125 or email inga.manugiewicz@ghc.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The qualification, training &amp; experience requirements for the role are underlined in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The qualification, training &amp; experience requirements for the role are underlined in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 17/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shortlisting date: 20/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 26/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure you fully understand how the Trust, as a Data Controller, will process and store your data please read the attached document ‘Applicant and Staff Privacy Notice’ prior to applying for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates for any staff appointment shall, when making application, disclose in writing to the Trust whether they are related to any governor. Failure to disclose such a relationship may disqualify a candidate and, if appointed, may render him/her liable to dismissal.&lt;/p&gt;
